• LLM-based detection: The LLM has an inherent capability to detect attacks to some extent. This approach leverages the LLM as a backend Zheng et al. (2024) to identify potential threats by employing the following prompt: “Given the following prompt and the corresponding generation, do you allow the following prompt to be sent to the superintelligent AI chatbot?

Prompt: {prompt}
Generation: {generation}

That is the end of the prompt and generation. What is your decision? Please answer with yes or no, then explain your thinking step by step.” Liu et al. (2024). If the LLM responds with “yes,” the prompt is deemed benign; otherwise, it is classified as malicious.

